FBIS4-37950 "drnes123_v_94001" FBIS-NES-94-123 Daily Report 26 Jun 1994 Pakistan Indian Troops Accused of Firing on Civilians Indian Troops Accused of Firing on Civilians BK2606114194 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in English 1100 GMT 26 Jun 94 BK2606114194 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network English BFN [Text] An ISPR [Inter-Service Public Relations] press release says the Indian soldiers resorted to unprovoked and indiscriminate firing with automatic weapons on the civilian population on village (Viladadoot) in the Nokial subsector as a result of which a six-year old child was killed. In another incident of firing by Indian troops from the across the Line of Control on village Karothi, a young man was critically wounded.
